reviews.text: Staff was very helpful, hotel is 2 year old(2017).  Has laundry machines onsite. It's located right near HK central library and adjacent to Victoria park.  Rooms are a bit small, but it is expected.

This is an excellent hotel in Causeway Bay on Hong Kong Island. The lobby is nice and the staff always helpful, and no line for check in. The price is on the low side (reasonable) for the location. As most Hong Kong hotels, the rooms are small-but smartly decorated and nicely laid out. The bathroom has cool glass that becomes obscure for privacy at the flick of a switch. The breakfast was good, not crowded, and they have a gym and laundry too. It's a few blocks from the subway and very close to trams and buses. I get to airport easily at 7 am.

Great value for such a clean, new, luxurious and convenient hotel. The standard room is on par with other Hong Kong hotels in terms of tight space, but everything is designed to maximize the efficiency. Will definitely consider staying here again in future trips to Hong Kong.
It was my best hotel in last two weeks in HK
Near the victoria park and we can walk around the beautiful park.
